# Cursor Rules for Image Detector Project

## Python Environment Configuration
- Always use the Python virtual environment named "yolox" located at `./yolox/`
- Set the Python interpreter path to `./yolox/bin/python`
- Activate the virtual environment before running Python scripts or installing packages

## Project-Specific Rules
- This project uses YOLOX for object detection training and inference
- Python dependencies are managed through the yolox virtual environment
- Always ensure the virtual environment is activated when working with Python files

## Development Guidelines
- Use the yolox virtual environment for all Python operations
- Install new packages using `./yolox/bin/pip install <package_name>`
- Run Python scripts using `./yolox/bin/python <script_name>`
- Maintain the virtual environment structure and dependencies

## File Organization
- Python source code is located in the `src/` directory
- YOLOX framework is in the `YOLOX/` directory
- Training configurations are in the `exps/` directory
- Model outputs are stored in `YOLOX_outputs/` directory

## Application specific logic
- never edit files in the train_yolox/exps directory. They must be generated by the data_prep script
